$ /dev/kmem

`/dev/kmem` provides access to *virtual* kernel memory, compare with `→ Linux/fhs/dev/mem`.

`/dev/kmem` is obsolete and replaced by `→ Linux/fhs/proc/kcore`.

Apparently, `/dev/kmem` is (was?) created in `→ Linux/kernel/source/drivers/char/mem_c`.

sa:
  `→ Linux/fhs/dev`

  `→ Linux/fhs/dev/mem`, `→ Linux/fhs/dev/port`

  `CONFIG_DEVKMEM`
